=== Rotating systems ===
A rotational quantity such as torque or angular momentum is described in geometric algebra as a bivector. Suppose a circular path in an arbitrary plane containing orthonormal vectors and is parameterized by angle.
: formula_265

By designating the unit bivector of this plane as the imaginary number
